# How-to-with-link

1. Download below templates and use them when preparing a print order and delivery schedule 
   ![template](https://templatedata.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/truck-delivery-schedule-template.jpg)
   ![ordertempate](https://www.techavy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Daily-Production-Schedule-Template-Excel-1280x720-1.png)  

2. Prepare the production file (PDF with bleeds.) If you do not remember how to prepare bleeds in pdf file check below link.
   Link to check: [Enfocus](https://blog.enfocus.com/bleed-in-a-pdf-file)  

3. Connect to FTP in a printing house in order to transfer your files. (In case you do not remember how to connect ot FTP, click below image to check  Youtube video for a detailed instruction) 
   Youtube Video to check: [![IMAGE_ALT](data:image/png;base64,)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3zqvsmkEYCY&ab_channel=InMotionHosting)
4. Upload created files via FTP. (If you do not remember how to upload a file via FTP, click below link for detailed instruction)
   Youtube video to check: (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NJLl9RT2mUc&ab_channel=MilesWeb)

5. If FTP transfer is not possible, try sending files via WeTranfer. For more information about connection WeTransfer click below image:
   WeTransfer instruction:[![IMAGE_ALT](data:image/jpeg;base64,)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gmzMsSCKj4E&ab_channel=CareHomeMarketingExpert)  


     
6. Check with the printing house the fastest posible delivery date **(check your imail for message  template)**  
7. Track works progress with printing house (set dates an exact hours for calls or emails)  
8. Collect prints from printing house  
9. Success!
